      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PERFECT FORCE (7) has opened her career impressively, finishing less than a length from the winner at both runs. Raced on the speed and wouldn't lie down but found one better over this distance at Gosford last start. Ready to win back in a country maiden. GO RUSSIAN (6) is still in her first prep but with the runs now being spaced she maintains a zest for racing. Led and gave a great sight but was nailed late over 900m at Newcastle last time. Will race handy again and is going to be tough to overcome. CHECKS'N'BALANCES (2) is a North Pacific three-year-old on debut for the Archibald camp. Trialling well and should have something to offer. Betting holds the key. BUNDORAN (4) has not raced since weakening to finish fifth over 1209m at Yarra Valley eight weeks ago. Now in the Gavin Groth stable. Placed four from six including twice at this trip so from gate one she is a chance. MOKE LAKE (1) is cherry ripe and from a nice draw should be thereabouts.",
